It has humor potential - the cartoonish trembling of its never-ending impact - but also the grace of jogging and diving, the two sports that essentially unite it.
The word "trampoline" comes from the Spanish word "El Trampolin", which means "jump board".
Aspiring winners jump on a giant trampoline, shoot up to almost 30 feet into the air, and must perform a series of falling movements (spin, stitch, and jump) before landing on their feet.
