Moving forward is not the goal.
He or she bounces off, seemingly weightless like an astronaut, goes up, then down, then effortlessly back up.
Here again, there is competition, of course not without difficulty, but during the exercise there is no hectic attack on the target, no long-distance bulging, only the dreamlike, elegant suspension of time and gravity.
