The worldwide turnover of the equipment is around 400 billion euros.
Add to this the successful business of the countless app providers and telecommunications companies.
A whole industry has now been built around the smartphone.
The decisive breakthrough to the mass market came only in early 2007, when Apple CEO Steve Jobs announced the introduction of the iPhone at Mac World.
He promised three devices in one: a music player, a phone, and an Internet communicator, all easily operated with a touch screen.
Apple's triumphal march began, and today the iPhone is still the company's most important product.
Nokia, Motorola and Blackberry, which dominated the market, had the aftermath.
They finally disappeared, Blackberry has to fight.
Apple and Asian vendors like Samsung are now in charge.
The smartphone is a given 20 years after its invention.
Today, on average, every German looks at his mobile phone 88 times a day.
"We all have to learn to put the smartphone away", said Janina Kugel, Siemens' board member responsible for personnel.
Permanent accessibility is now considered a curse and a blessing at the same time.
