A high demand for medical technology in Asia has boosted the turnover of Carl Zeiss Meditec.
In the first nine months of the financial year that began in October, the group's turnover rose by 6.7 percent to 798.6 million euros, the listed company said on Friday in Jena.
The Asian business grew disproportionately by 17.1%.
Profit before interest and taxes increased from EUR 89.5 million to EUR 110.5 million, according to the interim balance sheet.
The Jena medical technology group wants to surpass the turnover mark of one billion euros this financial year, the board confirmed.
Zeiss Meditec manufactures equipment and equipment for medical offices and clinics.
The company, which is part of the optics and electronics group Carl Zeiss (Oberkochen), employs almost 3000 people.
